comments.body: @escowles, is this something @roelmoon or I can do? is there any reason why we can't?
@kelea99 Sure, I'm sure either of you could do that any time you have a minute.
I remember us writing something similar to this recently. @escowles is this related to #3910 and #3909 and should the issues be merged in some way?

Yes, I think these are all basically the same issue ‚Äî downloading a single page is fine, but downloading several pages, or PDFs for several items, is very cumbersome. So I think the key thing I'm not clear about here is what the delivery mechanism should be. I was mostly thinking of staff doing the request, where Isilon or other local staging disk seemed like the right place to put things. But if end users have the same need, then maybe Google Drive or some other system like that would be better?
